150 grams Jasmine Rice
240 grams British Beef Mince
80 grams Sliced Mushrooms
50 grams Gochujang Paste
25 grams Ketjap Manis
30 grams Peanut Butter
15 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
120 grams Coleslaw Mix
100 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce

Boil a half-full kettle.
Pour it into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 12-13 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef and mushrooms, 6-8 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.
Meanwhile, open the remaining sachets.

Stir in the gochujang, ketjap, peanut butter, soy and water (see pantry).
Add the coleslaw mix.
Bring to the boil. Simmer, 1-2 mins.
Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the rice between your bowls.
Top with the beef stir-fry.
Enjoy!